# 🌌 Aletheia  
### *Revealing the science of life beyond Earth*

_Built for the [NASA Space Apps Challenge 2025](https://www.spaceappschallenge.org/)_

---

## 🌟 Overview

NASA has decades of **space biology experiments** — essential for planning safe human exploration of the Moon and Mars — but this knowledge is scattered and hard to navigate.

**Aletheia** (from the Greek ἀλήθεια — “truth” or “revelation”) is an **AI-powered dynamic dashboard** that organizes over 600 NASA bioscience publications into an **interactive, intelligent knowledge base**.

With **AI search, knowledge graphs, and engaging visual tools**, Aletheia helps scientists, mission planners, and learners unlock insights from NASA’s space biology research.

---

## ✨ Features

- 🔎 **Search with AI** — Ask natural-language questions; get instant answers sourced from NASA bioscience papers  
- 🕐 **Timeline** — Explore breakthroughs in space biology year by year  
- 🔗 **Knowledge Graph** — Visualize relationships between studies, topics, and missions  
- 🎙️ **Podcast Creator** — Turn scientific findings into short, engaging audio dialogues  
- 📚 **Comic Generator** — Convert research stories into easy-to-grasp comics  
- 🎴 **Flash Cards** — Study key space biology concepts interactively  
- 🧭 **NASA-inspired UI** — Accessible, mobile-friendly, and visually stunning

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer          | Technologies |
|----------------|-------------|
| **Frontend**   | [Next.js 15](https://nextjs.org/) · TypeScript · TailwindCSS v4 · shadcn/ui |
| **Backend**    | [LightRAG](https://github.com/HKUDS/LightRAG) — Retrieval-Augmented Generation & Knowledge Graph |
| **Data**       | 600+ NASA Space Biology open-access publications (CSV + PubMed links) |
| **Visualization** | Interactive timeline charts, network graphs, dynamic UI components |

---

## 🚀 Getting Started

### 1️⃣ Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+
- npm or yarn
- Python 3.10+ (if running LightRAG backend)

### 2️⃣ Setup Frontend

```bash
cd front_end
npm install
npm run dev
````

Open [http://localhost:3000](http://localhost:3000).

### 3️⃣ Setup LightRAG Backend

```bash
git clone https://github.com/HKUDS/LightRAG.git
cd LightRAG
pip install -e ".[api]"
lightrag-server
```

Configure your **OpenAI API key** or preferred LLM in `.env`.
Our app connects to LightRAG to power **AI search & knowledge graph**.

---

## 🌌 Data Source

* [NASA Space Biology Publications CSV](https://osdr.nasa.gov/)

Aletheia currently indexes **600+ open-access NASA space biology studies** to build the knowledge graph and power AI-driven insights.

